{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Ahrnsbrak Glacier | other_name = | photo = Heritage-Range-location-map.png | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Heritage Range in Western Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Ahrnsbrak Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Heritage Range]] | coordinates = {{coord|79|48|S|82|18|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Union Glacier]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Ahrnsbrak Glacier''' is a [[glacier]] in the [[Enterprise Hills]] of the [[Heritage Range]] in [[Antarctica]], flowing north between [[Sutton Peak (Antarctica)|Sutton Peak]] and [[Shoemaker Peak]] to the confluent ice at the lower end of [[Union Glacier]]. It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey]] from surveys and [[U.S. Navy]] air photos, 1961&ndash;66, and was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for William F. Ahrnsbrak of the [[United States Antarctic Research Program]], a [[glaciologist]] at [[Palmer Station]] in 1965.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
