'''João Pedro de Magalhães''' is a Portuguese [[microbiologist]] at the University of Liverpool. His lab at the University of Liverpool studies aging through both computational and experimental approaches. His ultimate goal is to cure human aging.
In 1999, he obtained his degree in Microbiology from [[Escola Superior de Biotecnologia]]. Under Olivier Toussaint, he obtained his PhD from the University of Namur in 2004. Then he did a [[Postdoctoral researcher|postdoc]] in the [[George M. Church|George Church]] lab from 2004 to 2008.<ref>[https://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.joao.pedro.de.magalhaes Lifeboat Foundation]</ref>
He helps maintain several databases on aging - among them - GenAge, AnAge, DrugAge,<ref name="pmid28299908">{{cite journal |vauthors=Barardo D, Thornton D, Thoppil H, Walsh M, Sharifi S, Ferreira S, Anžič A, Fernandes M, Monteiro P, Grum T, Cordeiro R, De-Souza EA, Budovsky A, Araujo N, Gruber J, Petrascheck M, Fraifeld VE, Zhavoronkov A, Moskalev A, de Magalhães JP | title=The DrugAge database of aging-related drugs. | journal= [[Aging Cell]] | volume=16 | issue=3 | year=2017 | pages=594–597 | url=http://www.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/acel.12585 | doi=10.1111/acel.12585 | pmid=28299908 | pmc=5418190}}</ref> CellAge, GenDR, the Digital Aging Atlas,<ref name="MyUser_Ageing-map.org_May_29_2015c">{{cite web |url=http://ageing-map.org/ |title=Welcome to the Digital Ageing Atlas, the portal of ageing related changes |newspaper=Ageing-map.org |date= |accessdate= May 29, 2015}}</ref> and Who's Who in Gerontology. His research group helped sequence the transcriptome of the long-lived bowhead whale. He also helps advise the Lifeboat Foundation.
Among his many longevity-related scientific research projects, Magalhães has sequenced and analyzed the [[genome]] of the [[bowhead whale]].<ref name="pmid25565328">{{cite journal |vauthors=Keane M, Semeiks J, Webb AE, Li YI, Quesada V, Craig T, Madsen LB, van Dam S, Brawand D, Marques PI, Michalak P, Kang L, Bhak J, Yim HS, Grishin NV, Nielsen NH, Heide-Jørgensen MP, Oziolor EM, Matson CW, Church GM, Stuart GW, Patton JC, George JC, Suydam R, Larsen K, López-Otín C, O'Connell M, Bickham JW, Thomsen B, de Magalhães JP | title=Insights into the evolution of longevity from the bowhead whale genome | journal= [[Cell Reports]] | volume=10 | issue=1 | year=2015 | pages=112–122 | url=http://www.cell.com/cell-reports/abstract/S2211-1247(14)01019-5 | doi=10.1016/j.celrep.2014.12.008 | pmid=25565328 | pmc=4536333}}</ref> And he has also contributed to analysis of the genome of the [[naked mole rat]].<ref name="pmid25172923">{{cite journal |vauthors=Keane M, Craig T, Alföldi J, Berlin AM, Johnson J, Seluanov A, Gorbunova V, Di Palma F, Lindblad-Toh K, Church GM, de Magalhães JP | title=The Naked Mole Rat Genome Resource: facilitating analyses of cancer and longevity-related adaptations | journal= [[Bioinformatics (journal)|Bioinformatics]] | volume=30 | issue=24 | year=2014 | pages=3558–3560 | url=http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/content/30/24/3558.long | doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/btu579 | pmc=4253829 | pmid=25172923}}</ref> Both of these mammals are exceptionally long-lived and exceptionally cancer-resistant.
