{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[New General Catalogue|NGC]] 166 | image = File:NGC_0166_DSS.jpg | epoch = [[J2000]] | ra = {{RA|00|35|48.8}}<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 0166 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/nph-objsearch?objname=NGC+166&img_stamp=yes&extend=no | accessdate=2016-09-02}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|-13|36|38}}<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[Cetus]] | z = 0.020084<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = | type = | appmag_v = 15.18<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 0.9' &times; 0.3'<ref name="ned" /> | notes = | names = [[Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 2143.<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''NGC 166''' (also known as '''PGC 2143''') is a [[spiral galaxy]] located around 2.6 million light-years away in the constellation [[Cetus]], with an apparent magnitude of 15.18.<ref name="ned"/> It was discovered by [[Francis Preserved Leavenworth]] in 1886.<ref>{{cite web|title=Francis Preserved Leavenworth|url=http://www.klima-luft.de/steinicke/ngcic/persons/leavenworth.htm|website=klima-luft.de|accessdate=2 September 2016}}</ref>
